      '<h2 style="color:#F59E0B;font-size:1.7rem;margin:2.5rem 0 1rem;border-left:4px solid #F59E0B;padding-left:1rem;">What Toppers Do Differently</h2>',
      '<p style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.85);font-size:1rem;line-height:1.85;margin-bottom:0.8rem;"><strong style="color:#F59E0B;">They treat Prelims and Mains as one integrated preparation.</strong> They write Mains answers from Month 4 onwards, even while preparing for Prelims. This means they are Mains-ready the moment Prelims results come out.</p>',
      '<p style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.85);font-size:1rem;line-height:1.85;margin-bottom:0.8rem;"><strong style="color:#F59E0B;">They build a current affairs system, not just a habit.</strong> They maintain a structured notebook organized by themes — Economy, Environment, International Relations, Science & Tech, Social Issues. This makes revision 10x faster before the exam.</p>',
      '<p style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.85);font-size:1rem;line-height:1.85;margin-bottom:0.8rem;"><strong style="color:#F59E0B;">They get their answers evaluated.</strong> Self-evaluation is limited. Toppers join test series where answers are evaluated by experienced mentors. The feedback loop — write, get evaluated, improve — is what builds Mains writing quality.</p>',
