      '<h2 style="color:#34D399;font-size:1.7rem;margin:2.5rem 0 1rem;">IAS Salary Progression — 30-Year Career Path</h2>',
      '<p style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.85);font-size:1rem;line-height:1.85;margin-bottom:0.8rem;"><strong style="color:#34D399;">Year 0–4 (SDM/Sub-Collector):</strong> Basic: ₹56,100. In-hand: ₹95,000–1,10,000. Perks: Government bungalow, official car with driver, domestic help allowance.</p>',
      '<p style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.85);font-size:1rem;line-height:1.85;margin-bottom:0.8rem;"><strong style="color:#34D399;">Year 5–9 (Additional Collector):</strong> Basic: ₹78,800. In-hand: ₹1,30,000–1,50,000. Perks: Larger bungalow, multiple staff, travel allowances.</p>',
      '<p style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.85);font-size:1rem;line-height:1.85;margin-bottom:0.8rem;"><strong style="color:#34D399;">Year 10–15 (District Collector/DM):</strong> Basic: ₹1,18,500. In-hand: ₹1,80,000–2,20,000. Perks: Full district residence, security detail, official vehicles.</p>',
      '<p style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.85);font-size:1rem;line-height:1.85;margin-bottom:0.8rem;"><strong style="color:#34D399;">Year 16–24 (Divisional Commissioner/Secretary):</strong> Basic: ₹1,44,200. In-hand: ₹2,20,000–2,80,000. Perks: State-level residence, full security, multiple official vehicles.</p>',
      '<p style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.85);font-size:1rem;line-height:1.85;margin-bottom:0.8rem;"><strong style="color:#34D399;">Year 25–30 (Chief Secretary/Cabinet Secretary):</strong> Basic: ₹2,25,000. In-hand: ₹3,50,000–4,50,000. Perks: Apex Scale residence, Z+ security, diplomatic privileges.</p>',
      '<h2 style="color:#34D399;font-size:1.7rem;margin:2.5rem 0 1rem;">Banking Sector — Fastest Salary Growth</h2>',
      '<p style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.85);font-size:1rem;line-height:1.85;margin-bottom:0.8rem;">Banking jobs have the fastest salary progression in government sector. An SBI PO starts at ₹52,000 in-hand but reaches ₹1,20,000+ in-hand within 10 years through promotions.</p>',
      '<p style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.85);font-size:1rem;line-height:1.85;margin-bottom:0.8rem;"><strong style="color:#34D399;">SBI PO Career Path:</strong> PO (₹52,000) → Scale II Officer (₹70,000) after 3 years → Scale III Officer (₹90,000) after 6 years → Scale IV Manager (₹1,20,000) after 10 years → Scale V Chief Manager (₹1,50,000+) after 15 years.</p>',
      '<div style="margin-top:3rem;padding:2rem;background:rgba(52,211,153,0.07);border:2px solid rgba(52,211,153,0.3);border-radius:15px;"><h3 style="color:#34D399;margin-top:0;">Salary vs Effort — Best ROI</h3><p style="color:#a7f3d0;font-weight:600;line-height:2.2;margin:0;">Highest absolute salary → IAS/IPS/IFS (but 3–4 attempts average)<br/>Best salary for effort → Bank PO (1–2 attempts average)<br/>Fastest to reach ₹1 lakh/month → RBI Grade B (within 2 years)<br/>Best work-life balance + high salary → SSC CGL AAO<br/>Highest starting salary → RBI Grade B (₹90,000+ in-hand from Day 1)</p></div>',
      '</article>'
